@NODE "Prefs"

  akSGXPrefs
  -----------
  akSGXPrefs is the Preferences Program for akSGX.datatype.

  GUI has been designed with StormWizard 2.0, so this program needs
  "wizard.library" V42+ (you can find a copy on Aminet under
  "biz/haage/WizardLibrary.lha" or even never versions under
  ftp.haage-partner.com).

  Icon by Bert Bosma <lmb@wxs.nl> (based on NewIcons).

  Task (process) specific settings also can be done - either using
  the preferences program (which allows to select the corresponding
  process from a list as long as it actually is running at the same
  time) or by hand, following the scheme below:

                           OPTIONAL
  ---------------- task specific settings files -----------------------
  Settings specific to different caller programs may be created
  by copying the global settings from "Datatypes/akSGX.prefs" to an
  optional task-related prefs file called

            "Datatypes/akSGX.prefs_Tasks/TaSkNaMe"

  where "TaSkNaMe" means the name of the program as e.g. shown by
  a system monitor (for obvious reasons, this does work best with
  workbench programs, which don't require name patterns as some
  CLI programs might do, like for example "CLI(3):Work:Browsers/XWebber").
  So, with AWeb for example, you would just edit your global settings
  file and then do the following:

    MakeDir ENV:Datatypes/akSGX.prefs_Tasks
    Copy ENV:Datatypes/akSGX.prefs ENV:Datatypes/akSGX.prefs_Tasks/AWebIP"

     [... and the same for ENVARC: ...]

  After that, AWeb will ignore the global settings and fetch its own
  from the given file.
  ---------------------------------------------------------------------

  Undocumented options (not available via akSGXPrefs):

   - CUSTOM_MODES=0x....
   - NOASPECT
   - DEBUG

  WARNING: if the pic-dt of your OS version does not support
           alpha channel handling, then always set STRIPALPHA=ON
           (no ARGB/RGBA)

@ENDNODE

@NODE "History"

 History
 =======
 V45.92 (5.4.2009):    - added support for new SGX sub-type (LZ77)
                       - removed spec (separate archive)
                       - fixed some bugs (also in AnyToSGX)
                       - AnyToSGX now only writes SGX sub-type

 V45.91 (18.3.2008):   - fixed possible blitter race condition
                         in Any2SVG (when handling DT images with
                         depths <= 8 bit)

 V45.89 (27.1.2008):   - fixed version string
                       - fixed AnyToSVG tool
                       - updatd TestDTAlpha tool and check for
                         PICDTALPHA

 V45.88 (20.1.2008):   - added TestDTAlpha tool and check for
                         PICDTALPHA

 V45.78 (2.10.2007):   - Prefs: - if stripalpha is on, the other
                                  option now is disabled
                                - added "Reset" option for
                                  default settings

                         WARNING: if the pic-dt of your OS
                                  version does not support
                                  alpha channel handling,
                                  then always set STRIP_ALPHA=ON
                                  (no ARGB/RGBA)

 V45.70 (1.8.2007):   - a depth of 1 no longer is increased to 2
                      - improved some semaphore protection
                      - no longer attempts to NULL cmaps/regs

                      - memory-related optimizations

                      - removed all V40 legacy code
                      - will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                      - removed 24 bit -> 8 bit dithering
                      - removed 24 bit -> HAM 6/8 conversion
                      - removed all V40-related settings
                      - bitplane gfx now converted to chunky
                        prior to export

                      - Prefs: removed all V40-related settings
                      - Prefs: will not run with pic-dt < V43 anymore
                      - Prefs: will not run with wizard-lib < V42 anymore

 V45.65 (28.7.2007):  - address change

                      - added Samples directory with sample file

 V45.62 (25.5.2007):  - optimized memory pool configuration

 V45.60 (29.4.2007):  - prefs program now creates env "tasks" dir
                        prior to saving task-specific prefs
                        (-> Bernd Roesch)

 V45.59 (17.4.2007):  - added 48/64 bit support for 16 bit RGB(A)
                        graphics; currently scaled down to 8 bit

 V45.58 (3.3.2007):   - added new undocumented setting, which
                        allows to swap the alpha value from
                        RGBA to ARGB if set (SWAPALPHA=ON);
                        the resulting bitmap will be of that type;
                        note that SVG internally uses RGBA,
                        which therefore now has been made
                        the default (previously it was ARGB)
                      - optimized memory allocations
                      - improved error handling
                      - fixed bug in AnyToSVG which would not
                        have recognized the alpha channel under
                        some non-MorphOS systems, especially
                        with pic-dt V45

 V45.57 (13.1.2007):  - AnyToSVG now supports also reading Alpha
                        Channel from source datatype image and
                        preserving it in the SVG image

 V45.56 (11.12.2006): - replaced Forbid/Permit pair by semaphore
                      - now really:
                        removed pre-OS 3.1 gfx-lib bug workarounds
                      - fixed a related pool memory leak
                      - strongly optimized V43 code for 8 & 24 bit
                      - added alpha channel support (can be
                        switched off in V43 mode using STRIPALPHA)
                      - added latest format specification for SVG
                        (same directory as .guide file) - includes
                        alpha channel (32 bit RGBA) now

 V45.55 (28.11.2006): - fixed some minor issues
                      - major rework of .guide file
                      - major rework of prefs program
                      - code of dt and prefs now MOS-aware
                      - removed some obsolete prefs options
                      - removed progressbar support
                      - upgraded datatype engine to latest code
                      - updated installer script
                      - OS versions below OS 3.1 no longer supported
                      - removed pre-OS 3.1 gfx-lib bug workarounds
                      - memory allocation now using pools
                      - replaced / optimized a lot of internal code
                      - now uses VMEM: instead of T: for temporary
                        files (avoid using RAM disk)
                      - now uses buffered IO reading/writing (8K)
                      - etc.

 V44.4 (9.8.98):      - *** FINAL RELEASE ***

                        It's suggested to convert images from SVG
                        to IFF-RGFX, if you'd like to make use of
                        Xpk compression. Both formats are supported
                        by SuperView-Library.

                        Further updates to akSVG-dt are unlikely.

                      - small changes

 V44.3 (28.7.98):     - stackswap in LibInit now only when necessary
                        and only to 8K (not 16K)
                      - rewrote major parts of the documentation;
                        check it out!
                      - fixed 1032 byte memory leak, as introduced
                        in one of the latest versions
                        (-> Troels Walsted Hansen)
                      - fixed problem in prefs file handling, that
                        could occur under low memory conditions

                      - you have to handle a large number of images ?
                        Organize, view, convert and process these ?
                        Do you want speed up through PPC support ?
                        Check out @{"PMPro" LINK Commercial_2/Main 0 }, the universal graphics tool and picture manager.

                      - did you already notice, that SViewNG now has PPC native
                        loaders/savers for e.g. PNG, JFIF, TIFF, PICT, too ?
                        They're even faster than the datatypes, since they
                        don't have to deal with OS bitmaps.

 V44.2 (15.7.98):     - removed commercial header in guide file
